tiny-dhcp

i find myself having to get devices ip addrs a lot. often times i get a router and use its dhcp server to do that task. what if i didn't need to find a router? thats where tiny-dhcp comes in. set your computer to 192.168.33.4/24, run zig build in the repo, then run ./zig-out/bin/tiny-dhcp and it should work.
